    description: "WhiteWater / Whistler Pipeline is a natural-gas transportation system connecting Permian Basin supply with downstream Gulf Coast and export demand corridors. Its customers include producers, marketers, LNG-linked users, and other midstream counterparties that require takeaway capacity from the Permian. The asset follows an asset-heavy midstream model based on pipeline transportation revenues and related long-term capacity commitments. Public materials identify Whistler as a core pipeline moving Permian gas toward the Agua Dulce market and later noted the combination of Whistler and Rio Bravo assets under a joint venture owned by WhiteWater and I Squared together with MPLX and Enbridge. I Squared acquired a controlling interest in Whistler in February 2023 through ISQ Global Infrastructure Fund III, and March 2024 disclosures described the post-combination ownership at 50.6% for WhiteWater/I Squared, 30.4% for MPLX, and 19.0% for Enbridge. The investment anchors I Squared’s exposure to U.S. natural-gas transportation linked to LNG and Gulf Coast demand growth.",
