    sector: "Midstream Energy",
    subsector: "LNG export terminal",
    region: "North America",
    country: "United States",
    ownershipVehicle: "KKR Global",
    description: "Port Arthur LNG is a liquefied natural gas export project under development on the U.S. Gulf Coast in Jefferson County, Texas. Its customer base consists of global LNG buyers, gas suppliers, and counterparties seeking long-term liquefaction capacity and U.S. Gulf Coast export access. The operating model is asset-heavy and project based, centered on large liquefaction trains, storage tanks, marine infrastructure, and long-term commercial contracts. Public project materials describe a four-train, two-phase facility with approximately 26 million tonnes per annum of nameplate capacity across Phases 1 and 2 and characterize the development as a $27 billion energy infrastructure investment. Sempra Infrastructure announced in September 2023 that it had completed the sale of a 42% indirect non-controlling interest in Port Arthur LNG Phase 1 to KKR after the project reached final investment decision.",
